.START 

Pratt & Lambert Inc. said it will purchase up to 300,000 shares, or about 5%, of the company's stock through open market or private transactions. 

In American Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday, Pratt & Lambert shares closed at $14.375, down 62.5 cents.
At yesterday's price, a buy-back of 300,000 shares would have a total value of $4.3 million.
The company is a maker of paint, coatings and adhesives. 

